      "code_changes": [
        {
          "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/tree-pass.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/cfgexpand.cc\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/combine.cc\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/final.cc\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/tree-pass.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"rtl_opt_pass\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/cfgexpand.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"pass_expand\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/combine.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"pass_combine\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/final.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"pass_final\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/cfgexpand.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"pass_expand::execute\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/combine.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"pass_combine::execute\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333\",\n      \"path\": \"gcc/final.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"pass_final::execute\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"GCC's RTL (Register Transfer Language) intermediate representation is processed through a series of optimization and code generation passes, all of which inherit from a common pass class hierarchy.\\n\\nThe RTL pass class is defined in gcc/tree-pass.h (lines 125-133) as 'rtl_opt_pass', which inherits from 'opt_pass'. The opt_pass base class (lines 73-113) provides the fundamental pass infrastructure with virtual methods for gate(), execute(), and clone(). All RTL-specific passes inherit from rtl_opt_pass to be treated as RTL-level transformations.\\n\\nThe first RTL pass in the pipeline is 'pass_expand' defined in gcc/cfgexpand.cc. This pass converts GIMPLE (the high-level intermediate representation) to RTL. The pass_expand class (lines 7010-7020) inherits from rtl_opt_pass and implements the execute() method. The pass_data_expand structure (lines 6994-7008) declares it as an RTL_PASS that requires PROP_ssa, PROP_gimple_leh, PROP_cfg, and related properties, and provides PROP_rtl. The execute() method at line 7023 handles the complete transformation from GIMPLE to RTL representation.\\n\\nA representative RTL optimization pass is 'pass_combine' found in gcc/combine.cc. This pass implements instruction combining, a critical optimization that merges multiple RTL instructions into more efficient sequences. The pass_combine class (lines 15268-15283) inherits from rtl_opt_pass and includes a gate() method that checks if optimization level > 0. The pass_data_combine (lines 15255-15266) defines it as an RTL_PASS with PROP_cfglayout required. The execute() method (line 15277) calls rest_of_handle_combine() to perform the actual instruction combining optimization.\\n\\nThe final code generation pass is 'pass_final' located in gcc/final.cc. This pass converts RTL instructions to assembly language and performs final transformations before output. The pass_final class (lines 4340-4353) inherits from rtl_opt_pass with its execute() method (line 4348) calling rest_of_handle_final(). The pass_data_final (lines 4327-4338) declares this as an RTL_PASS that requires no specific properties but generates the final assembly output.\\n\\nThe RTL pass chain follows a logical progression: after gimple-to-RTL expansion in pass_expand, multiple RTL optimization passes (like pass_combine) transform and improve the RTL representation, followed by the pass_final which generates the target-specific assembly code. This architecture allows GCC to maintain clear separation between high-level GIMPLE transformations and low-level RTL optimizations and code generation.\"\n}\n",
